<section name="Ruhi Book 2" id="4">
  <quote id="105">
    <introtext><![CDATA[]]></introtext>
	<text><![CDATA[O wayfarer in the path of God! Take thou thy portion of the ocean of His grace, and deprive not thyself of the things that lie hidden in its depths. Be thou of them that have partaken of its treasures. A dewdrop out of this ocean would, if shed upon all that are in the heavens and on the earth, suffice to enrich them with the bounty of God, the Almighty, the All-Knowing, the All-Wise. With the hands of renunciation draw forth from its life-giving waters, and sprinkle therewith all created things, that they may be cleansed from all man-made limitations and may approach the mighty seat of God, this hallowed and resplendent Spot.]]></text>
 	<author><![CDATA[Bahá’u’lláh]]></author>
  	<reference><![CDATA[Gleanings from the Writings of Bahá’u’lláh, p. 279]]></reference>
    <language>en</language>
    <url><![CDATA[http://reference.bahai.org/en/t/b/GWB/gwb-129.html]]></url>
  </quote>
